PN,39804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1781384336
OL,3,CInvestigation into 1996 bombing closed
OL,4,Cby counter terrorism police
OL,6,FJust before 10.00am, Gary Hall, a
OL,7,Fsecurity guard at ITV's Granada
OL,8,Fstudios, received a phone call from a
OL,9,Fman with a "very calm" Irish voice.
OL,10,FThe man said he had planted a bomb
OL,11,Fthat would explode an hour later.
OL,13,FShortly afterwards, police began
OL,14,Fevacuating about 80,000 people from
OL,15,Fthe city centre, while attempts were
OL,16,Fmade to find the bomb.
OL,18,FAmid the panic, a police officer
OL,19,Fspotted the white lorry and noticed
OL,20,Fwires running from the dashboard.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
